data.name: label7.Text
data.value: As for calorie burning, the rate varies depending on factors such as intensity, duration, and individual factors like weight and fitness level. On average, jumping rope can burn approximately 10-15 calories per minute for a person weighing around 150 pounds. However, this rate can increase with higher intensity or longer durations of jumping.

data.name: lblweightDescription.Text
data.value: Jumping rope is a fantastic cardiovascular exercise with numerous benefits. Jumping rope improves heart health by increasing your heart rate, which strengthens your heart muscle and enhances circulation.
